title: The Art of Etruria and early Rome (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Pdf / English / 1967 NY / 257 pages / 31 MB

by G. A. Mansuelli

57 illustrations in full color, 15 illustrations in black and white

What substance is there in the famous, almost legendary "originality" of Etruscan art? The question has been discussed for years. In this book Professor Mansuelli recognizes the "Villanova geometric style" as the matrix from which all subsequent Etruscan art was drawn. He emphasizes the importance of Greek influences, with the proviso that too close a relationship must not be looked for.
